      <div class="wrap">
        <h2>Servers and software from one hand</h2>
        <p class="lead">In large corporations those are two departments. For a smaller company it means: two vendors, two invoices, and when something breaks, two culprits pointing at each other.</p>
        <ul class="why-points">
          <li><strong>No blame game:</strong> not "it's the server" versus "it's the code". With me both are in the same hands.</li>
          <li><strong>Software that fits the environment:</strong> I don't develop past your infrastructure, because I run it myself.</li>
          <li><strong>The industry calls it DevOps:</strong> development and operations belonging together has long been standard. I live that at small scale, from the application down to the server beneath it.</li>
        </ul>
