    <section id="faq" data-section-key="faq">
      <div class="wrap">
        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <details><summary>You're just one person, what if you're unavailable?</summary><p>Fair question. My approach: I document everything so that someone else can take over in an emergency, instead of hoarding knowledge in my head. On top of that come the tested, off-site backups and a reachable emergency number. So your operation doesn't depend on my presence, but on a documented, recoverable setup.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What does it cost?</summary><p>Two simple models, both without counting hours: <strong>ongoing care</strong> is a monthly package from €149/month (base: e.g. 1 server + up to 5 workstations), I monitor your systems, install updates and check the backups. <strong>One-off jobs and projects</strong> get a one-page fixed-price quote after the free initial consultation. That way you know the price before I start.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What happens in an emergency or data loss?</summary><p>For acute issues you reach me directly by phone and I deal with it as a priority. Maintenance clients have a fixed response time: within 12 hours on business days. And as a precaution, tested backups are in place: we verify restores <em>before</em> the emergency and document how they work.</p></details>
        <details><summary>How do you handle data protection (GDPR)?</summary><p>Essential for practices and law firms: a data processing agreement (DPA) is part of every engagement, data stays on systems in Germany, backups are encrypted, and I work aligned with the German BSI baseline-protection methodology. Data protection isn't an add-on, it's the default.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Am I locked into a contract?</summary><p>No. Projects are one-off fixed-price engagements. Monthly care can be cancelled. I'd rather convince through work than through contract terms.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Will I understand what you're doing?</summary><p>Yes, that's part of the job. No jargon, everything documented in writing and explained so you can pass it on to your team.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you see our data when maintaining our systems?</summary><p>To maintain your IT I need access to systems, not to your content. I work on configuration, structure and scripts. Your actual data (database contents, documents, emails) stays on your systems and is not extracted or sent to cloud or AI services. If a specific task genuinely requires real data, it only happens by arrangement, documented, and under the data processing agreement. The AI tools I use only ever see code and structure, never your content.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Do you use AI for development?</summary><p>Yes, as a tool. AI takes the routine off my plate. The decisions (how something is built, what's secure) and the responsibility for them stay with me. <strong>The tools don't see your data</strong>, only code and structure.</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>

